The paper discusses the use of funnel plots to measure and visualize uncertainty in research performance of Italian universities in science disciplines. This methodology is commonly used in fields such as medical research and quality control, which are closely related to computer science sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
